The paper deals with distributed parameter estimation and spectrum estimation over wireless sensor networks, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of conjugate gradient algorithms for optimization and estimation also suggests the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the focus on real-time response and cooperative behavior of the algorithms suggests the category of control systems (cs.SY).
